title: Third Act: Accountability Postcards
description:
Third Act is a national grassroots organization dedicated to organizing and mobilizing Americans age 60+ to safeguard our democracy and protect our climate. We know with your support, we can connect with voters, build voter enthusiasm, and help elect democracy and climate champions!

Third Act is partnering with Activate America in writing to Democratic and Democratic leaning voters in key Republican swing districts to let them know what their Republican representatives are up to! This information may not be getting through to voters via other media. Right now we are sharing info on votes to cut Medicaid while giving big tax breaks to billionaires and also talking about tariffs. We are also asking voters to call their representatives and ask them not to cut Medicaid or support tax breaks for billionaires while regular people lose services.

Note volunteers supply their own postcards and stamps for this effort. Please mail postcards as you complete them and by June 15 at the latest.

Follow the instructions below to sign up and then see the available postcard campaign choices and request voter addresses. 

If you have questions about Third Act's work, please contact "mike at third act dot org"


**You will receive addresses and a postcard script from our partner, Activate America. You can supply your own postcards and stamps, or download and print a custom Third Act Vote postcard (see below).**

***INSTRUCTIONS***

Sign up and then click on "Complete Your Registration Here." You will then be directed to a second form called "Postcards to Voters." Choose any campaign, and let us know how many names and addresses you want us to send to you. You will also receive a confirmation text.  

After you choose your campaign and request your voter addresses, you will get a Confirmation Email from Activate America. The link to the form "Postcards to Voters" is in the Confirmation Email. Use this link to order more names and addresses in the future.

You will receive your script, instructions, and voter names and addresses in a separate email, within a few hours.

**If you don't see the email, please check your Spam and Trash folders** for an email from  addresses@activate-postcards.vote or [staffname]@activateamerica.vote before reaching out to us.

- The deadlines for mailing postcards vary, and are stated on the script you will receive. You can also look for the deadlines on the same page as the order form.

- ***You supply your own postcards and stamps.***

- Click here:  https://thirdact.org/act/write-postcards-to-voters-main for info on downloading a print-at-home Third Act VOTE postcard, buying stamps, and/or buying other postcard designs.

Learn more about Third Act’s work (https://bit.ly/3N81XHn), including increasing participation in elections, advocacy to ensure voting access, voter education, cultural engagement, and direct action.

- For questions about receiving your voter addresses, contact anna@activateamerica.vote. 
- For questions about Third Act's Protect the Vote work, please contact info@thirdact.org.

***TAKE ACTION NOW!***

Thank you!

**The Team at Third Act**

QUESTION SUBMISSION: https://forms.gle/mXfEh8fDFg9AEFRD8

Background: As recent federal policies attack immigration, language access, and affordable housing, immigrant families are experiencing a strong uncertainty in our city.

"Housing Speaks!" is a critical community panel event addressing the language access and housing rights for immigrant communities in San Francisco.

The Bill Sorro Housing Program (BiSHoP) is bringing together key leaders from immigrant-serving organizations to discuss immigration, language and housing access concerns with members of the San Francisco community.

Join us as we explore how community organizations are protecting their clients and what strategies can protect our most vulnerable neighbors, from direct services & case management, to tenant organizing and site preservation!

Panel discussion with community leaders (40-60 minutes)

Networking reception with food provided (30 minutes)

Don't miss this moment to learn, meet, and join the movement to protect housing access for immigrant communities in San Francisco!

Questions? For more information, please contact our Community Manager  via donate@bishopsf.org.

About the Organizer

Bill Sorro Housing Program (BiSHoP) is a non-profit increasing and defending affordable housing access for diverse, multilingual, low-income families in San Francisco.

Founded in 2009, they provide support with affordable housing, rental subsidy, and tenants’ rights cases for 800+ families across The City from their office in SoMa - offered in English, Tagalog, Arabic, Spanish, and French.

Family-friendly!

The address "9 Mountain Park Rd, Holyoke" will get you there if you're using Waze. (Mountain Park Road runs off Route 5, and is not accessible from I-91.) People have reported that some GPS systems bring you right under the bridge, but on I-91. That’s annoying!

description:
The attacks on our immigrant communities are escalating, but so is our determination to build people power! We’re seeing ICE kidnap people from our communities and disappear them to foreign prisons. Our CT Elected officials MUST stand on the right side of history.

Join us for a Community Immigration Forum in Bridgeport where we will hear from community members, elected officials, and allies on why Connecticut MUST take action to protect immigrant communities, and how YOU can take immediate action in support of our immigrant community members.

🔵 Date: Saturday, May 17th
🔵 Time: 12:00pm to 2pm
🔵 Location: TBD 

Connecticut has made remarkable progress - In the last 4 years, the HUSKY for Immigrants coalition successfully expanded HUSKY coverage to over 19,000 undocumented children ages 0-15 and to undocumented pregnant people. We cannot let CT move backward.
 
What are we fighting for?
🗣️ Protect our progress and maintain HUSKY Medicaid coverage for undocumented children age 15 and under, and pregnant individuals.

🗣️ Raise the age for HUSKY eligibility up to age 26, for all income-eligible residents regardless of immigration status.

Bridgeport is and must continue to be a welcoming place for all our residents, where all of us, regardless of race, religion, sexual orientation, and immigration status, can feel safe!!

*Sponsoring organizations of the event include: the HUSKY 4 Immigrants Coalition, TRUST Act, NOW Coalition, Make the Road CT, Housatonic Community College, and other local organizations.*

title: Stand Up for Democracy March and Rally
description:
Join Democracy Action Network (DAN) for a powerful day of democratic engagement, community solidarity, and peaceful action. 

On Flag Day 2025, we stand together to reaffirm our commitment to democratic principles, constitutional governance, and human rights for all.

In a time when democratic institutions face unprecedented challenges, we invite concerned citizens of all backgrounds, beliefs, and political affiliations to unite in defense of our shared democratic values. This nonpartisan rally brings together speakers, community leaders, and grassroots activists to inspire action and build momentum for democratic renewal.

The Stand Up for Democracy Rally and March will feature:

- Keynote addresses from prominent civil rights advocates and democracy experts
- Community-led workshops on civic engagement and grassroots organizing
- Interactive educational displays about democratic principles and voting rights
- Family-friendly activities and entertainment
- A peaceful march from Palisades Park to Santa Monica City Hall

Democracy isn't just something we have—it's something we do. Join us as we stand up for the democratic principles that unite us as Americans: equality under the law, freedom of expression, fair elections, and government that answers to its people.

Transportation: The Downtown Santa Monica Metro E Line station provides direct rail access from Downtown LA and is a short walk from the rally site. Additional bus service and bike parking will be available.

Accessibility: The event is fully accessible, with accommodations for all participants.

For more information: Visit democracyactionnetwork.org/standup2025 or email info@democracyactionnetwork.org

The Democracy Action Network (DAN) is a nonpartisan grassroots organization founded in 2024 dedicated to defending democratic institutions, promoting civic engagement, and fostering inclusive democracy through nonviolent action and community empowerment.

description:

title: Frontlines to Phone Lines: Veterans Caucus Phone & Text Bank Takeover
description:
📞📲 Frontlines to Phone Lines: Veterans Caucus Phone & Text Bank Takeover

Join the NJDSC Veterans Caucus for an evening of civic duty and public service as we lead a phone & text bank to connect with voters across New Jersey!

Grounded in the values of leadership, sacrifice, and commitment to country, this event brings together veterans and allies to mobilize voters and defend the democratic freedoms they’ve fought to protect.

Whether you’ve served in uniform or are joining in solidarity, your voice matters—and we’ll provide everything you need to take action.

## We’ll let you know whether it’s a phone bank or text bank when you join us that day!

What to Expect:

✅ A quick training at the start

✅ Scripted calls and texts

✅ Community of passionate volunteers

✅ Real-time support and encouragement

You will need access to a smartphone, computer or tablet and wifi. 

Together, we can put our values into action, one conversation at a time.
